<br>
  I'm a level 55 bard. I'm no Sebilis fanatic, but I hunt there often enough, and I know that I can pull my own weight crowd controlling in most of the camps there, the exceptions being some of the higher level areas (juggs, shrooms). I join a group forming at the zone in. Group consists of a warrior, a rogue, a cleric, a shaman, and me so far, leaving one slot open. We're heading to NG (probably the easiest camp in seb for chrissake!). The group leader decides that we NEED a chanter... Okay, there's a good way to piss off a bard. :) I know there are a lot of crappy bards that couldn't control a camp in Befallen at level 60, but I'm not one of them (heh, at least I hope not). Hell, in this case, we need a snarer more than a chanter; a ranger, necro, sk, druid, or wizard could have easily filled this slot. However, we NEED a chanter. We need a chanter so bad that we sit at the zone in for 45 minutes waiting for one. We need a chanter so bad that NG gets taken by another, less cowardly group. We need a chanter so bad, we won't even pull a few mobs to the zone in to pass the time and get some xp. We need a chanter SO bad, we won't even try the double spawn at the zone in... "What will we do with the second frog?" the group leader says. I dunno, I thought I'd give it a kiss - wtf do you think I'm going to do with it?? I wasn't given the ability to charm and mez so I could sit at the Sebilis zone in. The warrior pulls the mobs anyways. The two come to the group, and the cleric (group leader) says, "ZONE!" and then gates. Luckily the warrior and shaman had the guts to stay, and we killed both mobs while the rogue tries to make it to the zone (he dies on the way), and the cleric, who is bound in West Commons, says, "Geeze, that was a close one."<br>
<br>
  Okay, anyone whose that much of a wuss should not be going to Sebilis. Any cleric who would gate when he's FM and has a level 55+ warrior tanking should not be going to sebilis. Anyone who is doubtful of a bard's crowd controlling ability shouldn't invite him/her in the first place, you'll just waste his/her time. You want some Sebilis xp? You want some Sebilis loot? I'd say you need some balls more than either of those things. Have a nice day. ;) <p><html><b><green>Roliel Glorysong</b></green>
