<br>
Yeah, that sucks so much.<br>
<br>
Some classes get treated quite badly by the narrowminded gimps. Bards (and necros) in the way you mentioned, with the added &quot;all we want from you is cantana&quot; for bards. And for magicians, lol...<br>
<br>
Well, we all know that pets are bugged in some places and can be a bit pesky sometimes. But what really make it bad for the pet classes is that some people blame the pet EVERY time something bad happen and a pet is up, and demand that pets shall never be used at all in any situation whatsoever. <br>
<br>
A lesser version of this evil is that all mobs but one must always be mezzed and that the pet must always be deleted if it attack the wrong mob - even when it's a noncasting greenie that the pet can easily solo and theer is no risk for trains.<br>
<br>
Seems some people have read too much about raid guilds and think that they are cool and in the know if they treat a_light_blue_froglok00 with the fear and slow carefullness that would be appropriate for Vulak. Or raided too much themselves and forgotten how to be efficient in a less deadly enviorment. <br>
<br>
NEWSFLASH! You do in fact NOT need a level 60 warrior with full cleric and shaman buffs and five clerics chaincasting complete heal on him. Not if the mob you are going to kill is a level 45 brownie or a level 50 froglok. <p>Love, Edeina<br>
